Rate of Japan c / a surplus rise seen slowing . The recent rise in Japan ' s current account surplus is not linked to structural factors and the pace at which the surplus is rising is set to slow down , a Japanese international finance source said on Wednesday . " The current account has been rising in the past couple of months but we do not see any structural elements there , so we think the increase would slow down , " the source , who asked not to be identified , told reporters . The International Monetary Fund , in its annual review of the Japanese economy , said on Wednesday it saw no reason to worry about Japan ' s present current account surplus . But it foresaw possible retaliation by Japan ' s trading partners if the surplus began a sustained rise . ( ( - - Washington newsroom , + 1 202 898 8377 ) ) 
